25|$|On 6 October 1940, the Squadron {{received}} {{orders to}} pack supplies and equipment {{for a change}} of station to Savannah, Georgia. One officer and 100 enlisted men departed from Barksdale Field on <b>troop</b> <b>train,</b> while 11 officers and 54 enlisted men departed by privately owned vehicles. The men by <b>troop</b> <b>train</b> arrived at Savannah, Georgia on 8 October and set up at the Municipal Airport. The remainder of the personnel arrived on 19 October and the Squadron began ferrying aircraft to the National Guard Armory. By 20 October, equipment was set up and operations begun. The airfield was officially named Savannah Air Base.|$|E
